BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:FYHl9fTBLdLniydj85mV5
SUMMARY:Audubon Bird Walk
DTSTAMP:20260413T004308Z
DTSTART:20260416T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Learn more about the birds at the Bellevue Botanical Garden. Jo
	in Eastside Audubon for a monthly walk that explores the birds and their h
	abitat in the Garden. This one-mile walk will be on trails with various su
	rfaces and may include gravel\, mulch\, or pavement. Please dress for the 
	weather and wear comfortable walking shoes. Parking in the lot is free. Fr
	om the parking lot enter the garden through the breezeway and turn left. M
	eet your guide in the covered Gathering Place. This walk is for any level 
	of birder and no experience is necessary. Bring binoculars if you have the
	m. There will be some available to loan for the walk. Each walk is $5 per 
	person. Registration is required.  \n\nSorry\, the June walk is full. View
	 our calendar to register for upcoming walks.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/audubon-bird-walk/15998889/2026-04-16T00\n\nFrom SEAt
	oday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/audubon-bird-walk/1599888
	9/2026-04-16T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:27DfON4PPfe7cymoiqCAQ
SUMMARY:Earth Month Event | Nature Journaling
DTSTAMP:20260413T004308Z
DTSTART:20260416T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Nature Journaling in Pioneer Park\n\nIt's Earth Month! And to  
	celebrate we're hosting the first of our seasonal Nature Journaling educa 
	tional events. We will be exploring Pioneer Park with notebooks and pens m
	 aking observations about what we see. Participants will get instructions 
	o n how to begin nature journaling as well as a series of prompts to help 
	gu ide your observations.\n\nWhat is nature journaling? It is a practice i
	n  which you observe nature and spend some time crafting notes whether tha
	t' s words\, drawings\, painting\, quantitative data\, etc. \n\nClick here
	  to learn more: https://johnmuirlaws.com/nature-journaling-starting-growi
	ng /\n\nAll ages welcome\, no experience necessary.\n\nWhen: Thursday\, Ap
	ril 16th\, 10am-12pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park NW\, Meet at the corner of Isl
	and Crest Way and SE 68th St. Follow VOLUNTEER EVENT Signs\n\nWhat to brin
	g: Dr ess for the weather in comfortable clothes. Please bring a notebook\
	, and pens/pencils/water colors/crayons/etc \n\nRegistration: https://volu
	nteersig nup.org/J7KYK\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ea
	rth-month-event-nature-journaling/18066409/2026-04-16T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday 
	- Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-nature-
	journaling/18066409/2026-04-16T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
