UID:4BYy88oydrAffRQxJ72tD
SUMMARY:Earth Month Event | Plant ID Walk
DTSTAMP:20260413T004308Z
DTSTART:20260421T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Earth Month Plant ID Walk\n\nSpring is in bloom\, and we're exi
	ted to go explore Pioneer Park looking for our native flowers. Join us w e
	 walk through the northeast quadrant\, identifying native plants\, sharing
	 plant identification tips\, and sharing about the different roles plants 
	play in maintain healthy ecosystems.\n\nAll ages welcome\, no experience n
	ecessary.\n\nWhen: Tuesday\, April 21st\, 1-3pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park NE\
	, Meet at the corner of Island Crest Way and SE 68th St. Follow VOLUNTEER 
	EVENT Signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in clothes you're comf
	o rtable walking in. You might want to bring a note book for notetaking\, 
	or a camera to take pictures of the flowers!\n\nRegistration:  https://vol
	unte ersignup.org/J7KYK\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/e
	arth-month-event-plant-id-walk/18066411/2026-04-21T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - S
	ports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-plant-i
	d-walk/18066411/2026-04-21T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
