BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:FLmfiFsPbz__dFfltkehQ
SUMMARY:Issaquah Sustainability Fair
DTSTAMP:20260413T004308Z
DTSTART:20260425T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:This free event\,  in partnership with the Farmers Market\, is 
	held each year in tandem with our Earth Month celebration. You’re invited 
	to join us for a day packed with fun\, education\, and inspiration! Here a
	re some 2026 Sustainability Fair highlights: -Pedal towards a brighter fut
	ure: Join Trek’s Bicycle and Gerk’s Ski and Cycle for e-bike testing and p
	repare for the next round of e-bike rebates. Families can also demonstrate
	 their bike safety skills by participating in the Issaquah Police Departme
	nt Bike Rodeo.  -Save materials from the landfill while looking good doing
	 it! Pick through items in the free clothing section hosted by the Interac
	t Club and the Community Clothing Closet. After picking up some new clothe
	s\, visit the Furniture Repair Bank booth to find your next household stat
	ement piece.  -Explore the new frontier of EVs at the Touch-a-Truck area! 
	Learn about the first EV side-loading waste hauler in Washington State and
	 visit the Recology booth to hear about healthy\, clean\, waste-reducing p
	roducts you can buy locally.  -Connect with our natural world. Meet one of
	 the many environmental nonprofits in Issaquah\, take home a free tree\, a
	nd participate in a local conservation program all in one place! -Become a
	 leading climate household. Discuss how to make your household a climate l
	eader and save money while doing it by connecting with equipment installer
	s like All Climate Heating and Air Conditioning and Northwest Electrical a
	nd Solar. Learn more: bit.ly/IssySustainabilityFair\n\nhttps://seatoday.6a
	mcity.com/events/#/details/issaquah-sustainability-fair/18529115/2026-04-2
	5T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/issaquah-sustainability-f
	air/18529115/2026-04-25T00
LOCATION:Pickering Barn\, 1730 10th Ave NW\, Issaquah\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H
END:VEVENT
